{"audioUrl":"6a089305e9356a48684e4147_audio.mp3","createdAt":"2026-05-16T15:53:41.622Z","diarizationStatus":"NONE","group":"Default group","id":"6a089305e9356a48684e4147","interactions":[],"language":"en","originalAudioFileName":"Online Meeting Onboarding.mp3","segments":null,"summary":"Angela introduces the two new customer care hires, Ken and Maria, and Tarek from human resources, who joins briefly to outline onboarding steps. Tarek explains that before starting work, Ken and Maria must sign and return the liability policy and confidentiality agreement. The document requires four initials and two signatures, to be completed electronically. Once signed, it should be emailed to tarek.godas at mail.ca (also shown as tarek.gulduz at mail.ca). Work cannot begin until the signed file is on record. Ken is asked to email so Tarek can verify the address in file.\n\nAfter the HR portion, Angela explains the roles: Maria and Ken will handle client questions and provide demos of the software to team leads and other customers. She then gives a brief company/product overview: Jen and Nina founded Logiteam three years ago, a training software for work teams. The company has 43 employees, 82 customers, and five product packages. Over the next two weeks, Ken and Maria will become Logiteam experts, covering basic functions, security features, add-ons, and common glitches to help clients use the product to its full potential. Any questions so far?\n\nQ&A confirms logistics: they will use a company laptop, not personal devices, and accounts will be set up on the company machine. A video conferencing tool will be used and covered in training. Overall, the new hires will be prepared to assist clients after completing the training program.","title":"Onboarding New Customer Care Team for Logiteam","transcript":"Thank you all for joining. If you haven't met yet, we have our two newly hired customer care team members, Ken and Maria. Hi, guys. Welcome to the team. Thanks, Angela. It's great to be here. Hi, everyone. And Tarek from the customer care team. Hi, everyone. I'm Tarek from the customer care team. Hi, everyone. I'm Tarek from the customer care team. Thanks, Angela. It's great to be here. Hi, everyone. And Tarek from human resources is joining us for a brief period of time. Hi, Tarek. Morning, everyone. I scheduled this meeting to introduce our new team members to our training process. Tarek requested to be part of this meeting because he has some information for you as well. Tarek, would you like to begin? Sure. Thank you, Angela. So, Maria, Ken, welcome to Lock18. I want to talk to you about some forms that you need to fill out before you can begin work. You have received an email last week with our liability policy and our confidentiality agreement. The one about you agreeing not to share any confidential information about our company with any third parties. Have you received it? Yes, I have. I don't think I received that. I'm sorry. No problem. I will send it to you today. Once you have the document, please read it carefully and sign it electronically. There are four places where you will need to insert your initials and two where we need your signature. Once signed and saved, please send the document directly to me. My email address is tarek.godas at mail.ca. That is t-a-r-e-k dot g-u-l-d-u-z at mail.ca. This is very important because you cannot work until I have the signed document on file. Do you have any questions? No. I'll send it to you this afternoon. Perfect. Thank you. Ken, please send me an email so I can double check the email address I have in your file. Absolutely. Thanks. Okay. That's it. Thank you, Angela, for giving me the time. I will leave the meeting now. Have a good day, everyone. Maria, Ken, good luck with your training. Thanks, Tarek. Speak to you soon. Thanks. Thanks. Bye. Great. So let's get back to our business. Maria and Ken, you were both hired for the customer care positions. This means that you'll deal with our clients, team leads, and other companies who have purchased our software. You will answer some of their questions or provide a short demo of how our software and its features work. First, let me tell you a little bit about our product and our company. Then we'll go through your duties and responsibilities. And finally, you can ask me questions if you have any. Sounds good. So the two owners, Jen and Nina, created our company three years ago. They created software for training work teams called Logiteam. It became an instant success, and now we have 43 employees, 82 customers, and five different product packages. Our product is simple to use with some training, and that's where you come into the picture. In the next two weeks, you'll become experts of Logiteam. We'll make sure that you're familiar with all basic functions, security features, add-ons, and the most common glitches too. By the end of this training, you'll be able to assist our clients with using the software to its full potential. Do you guys have any questions so far? Yes, I have a question. Do we use our own devices or the company's laptop during the training? Great question. You don't need your own device. We will set up your account on the computer you'll be using for work, so it's better to start working on that. Great, thanks. I have a question. Will I be interacting with clients over the phone or video conference? We use a video conferencing tool that will be covered during your training. Okay, thank you.","uploadedAt":"2026-05-16T15:54:12.004Z","userId":"69ea8c5e35b2640397710047"}

