ow our software and its features work. First, let me tell you a little bit about our product and our company. Then we'll go through your duties and responsibilities. And finally, you can ask me questions if you have any. Sounds good. So the two owners, Jen and","source":"speaker"},{"start":187.107,"end":187.765,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242c","speakerName":null,"text":"Nina, created","source":"speaker"},{"start":189.318,"end":229.885,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242b","speakerName":null,"text":"our company three years ago. They created software for training work teams called Logiteam. It became an instant success, and now we have 43 employees, 82 customers, and five different product packages. Our product is simple to use with some training, and that's where you come into the picture. In the next two weeks, you'll become experts of Logiteam. We'll make sure that you're familiar with all basic functions, security features, add-ons, and the most common glitches too. By the end of this training, you'll be able to assist our clients with using the software to its full potential. Do you guys have any questions so far? Yes, I have a question. Do we use our own devices or","source":"speaker"},{"start":230.645,"end":235.758,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242d","speakerName":null,"text":"the company's laptop during the training? Great question. You don't need your own device. We","source":"speaker"},{"start":236.348,"end":244.347,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242b","speakerName":null,"text":"will set up your account on the computer you'll be using for work, so it's better to start working on that. Great, thanks.","source":"speaker"},{"start":245.242,"end":245.967,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242d","speakerName":null,"text":"I have","source":"speaker"},{"start":247.216,"end":252.211,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242f","speakerName":null,"text":"a question. Will I be interacting with clients over the phone or video conference? We","source":"speaker"},{"start":252.734,"end":256.227,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242b","speakerName":null,"text":"use a video conferencing tool that will be covered during","source":"speaker"},{"start":256.733,"end":257.915,"speakerId":"6a083d27f1ad65de8355242f","speakerName":null,"text":"your training. Okay, thank you.","source":"speaker"}],"summary":"Angela introduces the two new customer care hires, Ken and Maria, and notes that Tarek from Human Resources will join briefly to share onboarding details. Tarek explains that new hires must complete forms related to the liability policy and confidentiality agreement, which were emailed last week. Maria says she did not receive the document; Tarek will resend it today. The agreement requires four initials and two signatures, signed electronically and emailed to tarek.godas at mail.ca. The document must be on file before work can begin. Ken is asked to email Tarek to verify the address on file. Tarek then leaves the meeting.\n\nMaria and Ken are briefed on their training and duties. They will work with clients, team leads, and other companies using the Logiteam software, providing questions answers and short demos. The company background is shared: founders Jen and Nina started Logiteam three years ago; it now has 43 employees, 82 customers, and five product packages. Over the next two weeks, Ken and Maria will become Logiteam experts, covering basic functions, security features, add-ons, and common glitches, with the goal of enabling them to assist clients effectively by the end of training. A few questions are addressed: they will not need to use their own devices; accounts will be set up on a company computer. A video conferencing tool will be used for client interactions, and details will be covered during training.\n\nAction items: Tarek to send the liability/confidentiality document; Maria and Ken to sign electronically and return to Tarek; Ken to confirm his email address on file; training to proceed over the next two weeks with emphasis on product knowledge and client support.","title":"Onboarding and Training for New Customer Care","transcript":"Thank you all for joining. If you haven't met yet, we have our two newly hired customer care team members, Ken and Maria. Hi, guys. Welcome to the team. Thanks, Angela. It's great to be here. Hi, everyone. And Tarek from the customer care team. Hi, everyone. Hi, everyone. Hi, everyone. Hi, everyone. Hi, everyone. Hi, everyone. And Tarek from human resources is joining us for a brief period of time. Hi, Tarek. Morning, everyone. I scheduled this meeting to introduce our new team members to our training process. Tarek requested to be part of this meeting because he has some information for you as well. Tarek, would you like to begin? Sure. Thank you, Angela. So, Maria, Ken, welcome to Lock A team. I want to talk to you about some forms that you need to fill out before you can begin work. You have received an email last week with our liability policy and our confidentiality agreement. The one about you agreeing not to share any confidential information about our company with any third parties. Have you received it? Yes, I have. I don't think I received that. I'm sorry. No problem. I will send it to you today. Once you have the document, please read it carefully and sign electronically. There are four places where you will need to insert your initials and two where we need your signature. Once signed and saved, please send the document directly to me. My email address is tarek.godas at mail.ca. That is T-A-R-E-K dot G-U-L-D-U-Z at mail.ca. This is very important because you cannot work until I have the signed document on file. Do you have any questions? No, I'll send it to you this afternoon. Perfect. Thank you. Ken, please send me an email so I can double check the email address I have in your file. Absolutely. Thanks. Okay, that's it. Thank you, Angela, for giving me the time. I will leave the meeting now. Have a good day, everyone. Maria, Ken, good luck with your training. Thanks, Tarek. Speak to you soon. Thanks. Thanks. Bye. Great. So let's get back to our business. Maria and Ken, you were both hired for the customer care positions. This means that you'll deal with our clients, team leads, and other companies who have purchased our software. You will answer some of their questions or provide a short demo of how our software and its features work. First, let me tell you a little bit about our product and our company. Then we'll go through your duties and responsibilities. And finally, you can ask me questions if you have any. Sounds good. So the two owners, Jen and Nina, created our company three years ago. They created software for training work teams called Logiteam. It became an instant success, and now we have 43 employees, 82 customers, and five different product packages. Our product is simple to use with some training, and that's where you come into the picture. In the next two weeks, you'll become experts of Logiteam. We'll make sure that you're familiar with all basic functions, security features, add-ons, and the most common glitches too. By the end of this training, you'll be able to assist our clients with using the software to its full potential. Do you guys have any questions so far? Yes, I have a question. Do we use our own devices or the company's laptop during the training? Great question. You don't need your own device. We will set up your account on the computer you'll be using for work, so it's better to start working on that. Great, thanks. I have a question. Will I be interacting with clients over the phone or video conference? We use a video conferencing tool that will be covered during your training. Okay, thank you.","uploadedAt":"2026-05-16T15:40:40.060Z","userId":"69ea8c5e35b2640397710047"}

